The school moved to the High Court and sought for the judgment to be set aside.According to court documents, the minor’s parent contended the school discriminated the child because of his HIV status. The High Court has overturned a Sh5 million award to a minor by a tribunal that had ruled that the boy had been denied admission to a school in Kajiado because of his HIV status.
On June 8, 2018, the HIV and AIDS Tribunal had ruled against Namarat Academy School, finding that the minor’s rights, protected under the HIV and AIDS Prevention and Control Act, had been violated by the institution.



