But Justice E. C. Mwita, sitting in a Kajiado High Court, has ruled that the minor’s parent did not prove to the court that the school discriminated against the pupil due to his HIV status.
“From the totality of the circumstances of the case before the tribunal, the respondent failed to prove direct discrimination or sufficient conduct from the appellants for drawing an inference of discrimination,” Justice Mwita said in his judgment on December 18, 2020.



