“Another pupil was given a vacancy in the same class, the minor had been denied an opportunity on grounds that the school was full,” the parent told the court.
The parent said she was prepared to take the child for admission on January 13, 2016 after paying school fees.
According to them, their child was denied admission after they disclosed to the school his HIV status.
